	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002285_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>8 Dover St</placeName>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>Piccadilly</placeName>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><date when="1865-05-04">4 May 1865</date></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi>Hamilton</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Will you kindly 
<lb/>forward this note 
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi>Brodie</persName>?</p>
<lb/><p>A gentleman 
<lb/>called <persName>Robert 
<lb/>Arthington</persName>of 
<lb/><placeName>Leeds</placeName>wishes to 
<lb/>make an effort 
<lb/>to introduce the 
<lb/><bibl>bible</bibl> into <placeName>Angola</placeName></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><addSpan spanTo="#p01-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left hand margin'--></addSpan><p rend="no-indent">not knowing M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> <choice><sic><persName>Brodie</persName>s</sic><corr>Brodie's</corr></choice> address 
<lb/>I venture to trouble you<reg>.</reg> With kind 
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>regards to 
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi>H</persName> &amp; 
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>family 
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p><anchor xml:id="p01-01"/>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002285_0002"/><!--pb/@n='02'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">He has been led to 
<lb/>this from reading 
<lb/>my account of 
<lb/>that country. He 
<lb/>seems of a very 
<lb/>ardent temperament 
<lb/>uses the word 
<lb/>Hallelujah! in his 
<lb/>letters and is 
<lb/>possessed of 
<lb/>means. I don<reg>'</reg>t 
<lb/>know him at 
<lb/>all more that he 
<lb/>sometimes writes 
<lb/>to me, and in the 
<lb/>course he proposed 
<lb/>to adopt I feared </p>
<lb/><addSpan spanTo="#p02-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left hand margin'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>Sir Roderick</persName>had a thousand at 
<lb/>his reception last night<reg>.</reg></p><anchor xml:id="p02-01"/>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002285_0003"/><!--pb/@n='03'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">that he might lose a 
<lb/>deal of money &amp; do 
<lb/>no good. I therefore 
<lb/>advised caution 
<lb/>in dealing with the 
<lb/><term type="people">Portuguese</term>. This 
<lb/>advice he has 
<lb/>taken in good spirit 
<lb/>and now asks me 
<lb/>to tell him what 
<lb/>salary outfit 
<lb/>passage money &amp;c 
<lb/>ought to be given 
<lb/>to a man who 
<lb/>has been agent for 
<lb/>British &amp; F. Bible 
<lb/>Society who proposed 
<lb/>to settle at <placeName>Loanda</placeName></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><addSpan spanTo="#p03-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left hand margin'--></addSpan><p rend="no-indent">Everybody was there &amp; <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi>Beke</persName>
<lb/>the would be source of the <placeName>Nile</placeName> man<reg>.</reg></p><anchor xml:id="p03-01"/>


	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002285_0004"/><!--pb/@n='04'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I advise him now 
<lb/>to apply to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi>Silva</persName>
<lb/>through your elder 
<lb/>and tell him that 
<lb/>I don<reg>'</reg>t know any 
<lb/>thing of <choice><sic><persName>Silva</persName>s</sic><corr>Silva's</corr></choice> religious 
<lb/>feelings but that 
<lb/>the <term type="people">Portuguese</term> 
<lb/>generally have very 
<lb/>weak religious 
<lb/>convictions and 
<lb/>I have given him 
<lb/>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> <choice><sic><persName>Brodie</persName>s</sic><corr>Brodie's</corr></choice> card 
<lb/>with the assurance 
<lb/>that he will have 
<lb/>christian sympathy 
<lb/>with him. The 
<lb/>card is gone and </p>
			
	<pb n="0005" facs="liv_002285_0005"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName><choice><abbr>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi></abbr><expan>Reverend</expan></choice> D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Hamilton</persName>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>48 Euston Square</placeName>
<lb/><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> <choice><abbr>L</abbr><expan>Livingstone</expan></choice> <space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><unclear cert="medium">N</unclear></persName></p>


</div>
